title: Purdue rally falls short at Michigan State
text:
Purdue rally falls short at Michigan State 
By Dean Pantazi - 21 Alive Purdue University Boilermakers October 3, 2015 Updated Oct 3, 2015 at 10:23 PM EDT 
EAST LANSING, Mich. (21 Alive) - Michigan State's Arjen Colquhoun batted away a fourth down pass by Purdue's David Blough late in the fourth quarter to help preserve the second ranked Spartans' 24-21 win over the Boilermakers on Saturday. 
Michigan State raced to a 21-0 halftime lead, but a Blough touhdown pass and two Markell Jones scoring runs got Purdue back in the game befpre the late rally bid for the win came up short.
